    • Class handist.collections.dist.GlobalOperations extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialization Methods

        • writeReplace

          public abstract Object writeReplace()
                             throws ObjectStreamException
          Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

          This method is defined as abstract in class GlobalOperations to force the implementation in child classes. Implementation should return a MemberOfLazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the distributed collection on the remote place and return the "GLOBAL" member of this handle's local class.

          Throws:
          ObjectStreamException - if such an exception is thrown during the process

      • Serialized Fields

    • Class handist.collections.glb.DistColGlbTask extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -792674800264517475L

      • Serialized Fields

        • assignedAssignments

          ConcurrentLinkedQueue<E> assignedAssignments
          Contains the list of all the assignments that are being processed by a worker

        • assignmentsLeftToProcess

          Map<K,V> assignmentsLeftToProcess
          Map which associates the number of assignments left to process to each operation in progress.

          As workers complete operations of assignments, they will decrement the matching atomic counter. When a worker completes the last assignment available for an operation (i.e. the counter was decremented to 0), local completion of this operation is reached. That worker will therefore trigger the stealing process by releasing the operation thread which is currently blocking on a OperationBlocker.

        • availableAssignments

          ConcurrentLinkedQueue<E> availableAssignments
          Contains the list of all the assignments that are available to workers

        • completedAssignments

          ConcurrentLinkedQueue<E> completedAssignments
          Contains all the assignments that have been completely processed by a worker.

          The assignments in this collection have all of the current operations completed.

        • totalAssignments

          AtomicInteger totalAssignments
          Total number of assignments located on this place

        • collection

          DistCol<T> collection
          Underlying collection on which the assignments operate
